<figureCitation id="A7831FACFEDF871BDA27C77BFC767858" box="[818,913,1363,1389]" captionStart="FIGURE 180" captionStartId="266.[136,235,1331,1355]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,159,1299]" captionTargetId="figure-314@266.[151,1436,159,1299]" captionTargetPageId="266" captionText="FIGURE 180. Drawing of a species of Nezumia illustrated by Toshiji Kamohara (deposited at BSKU). The illustrated specimen, which was destroyed during WWII, was the basis for the first Japanese record of N. burragei by Kamohara (1937). [Photo: BSKU]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6423172" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6423172/files/figure.png" pageId="265" pageNumber="266">Fig. 180</figureCitation>
