<subSubSection id="77A250A2FEDF8718DA3FC7BFFAE87AE7" lastPageId="266" lastPageNumber="267" pageId="265" pageNumber="266" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="3F070329FEDF871BDA3FC7BFFA457AC1" blockId="265.[810,1452,1431,2070]" pageId="265" pageNumber="266">
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEDF871BDA3FC7BFFC137887" author="Kamohara, T." box="[810,1012,1431,1458]" pageId="265" pageNumber="266" pagination="186 - 190" refId="ref290602" refString="Kamohara, T. (1937) On some rare and one new species of fishes from Japan. Dobutsugaku Zasshi [Zoological Magazine, Japan], 49, 186 - 190. [In Japanese with English abstract.]" type="journal article" year="1937">Kamohara (1937)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFEDF871BDD78C7B0FA4C7887" authority="(Gilbert, 1905)" baseAuthorityName="Gilbert" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[1133,1451,1431,1458]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="265" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="burragei">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEDF871BDD78C7B0FB137884" box="[1133,1268,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="265" pageNumber="266">N. burragei</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEDF871BDC12C7BFFA447887" author="Gilbert, C. H." box="[1287,1443,1431,1458]" pageId="265" pageNumber="266" pagination="573 - 713" refId="ref285669" refString="Gilbert, C. H. (1905) The deep-sea fishes of the Hawaiian Islands. In: Jordan, D. S. &amp; Evermann, B. W. (Eds.), The Aquatic Resources of the Hawaiian Islands. Bulletin of the U. S. Fish Commission, 23. Government Printing Office, Washington DC, pp. 573 - 713, figs. 230 - 276, pls. 66 - 101. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 12624" type="book chapter" year="1905">Gilbert, 1905</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="47AF43B9FEDF871BDA78C792FC4B78E1" box="[877,940,1466,1492]" name="Japan" pageId="265" pageNumber="266">Japan</collectingCountry>
based on a single 
<quantity id="F840AECCFEDF871BDD80C791FB1078E1" box="[1173,1271,1465,1492]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="265" pageNumber="266" unit="mm" value="350.0">350 mm</quantity>
long specimen obtained at the Mimase fish market, 
<collectingCountry id="47AF43B9FEDF871BDDFDC7F3FAD778C0" box="[1256,1328,1499,1525]" name="India" pageId="265" pageNumber="266">Kochi</collectingCountry>
. This is a very rare species, which elsewhere is known only from the 
<typeStatus id="E003BD8BFEDF871BDA4EC437FC5A7B0C" box="[859,957,1567,1593]" pageId="265" pageNumber="266">holotype</typeStatus>
from Hawaii at a depth of 
<quantity id="F840AECCFEDF871BDC30C437FA4B7B0F" box="[1317,1452,1567,1594]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.7299999999999995" metricValueMax="6.029999999999999" metricValueMin="5.43" pageId="265" pageNumber="266" unit="m" value="573.0" valueMax="603.0" valueMin="543.0">543–603 m</quantity>
(USNM 51641, 
<quantity id="F840AECCFEDF871BDAF3C46AFBAA7B69" box="[998,1101,1602,1628]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.42" pageId="265" pageNumber="266" unit="mm" value="44.2">44.2 mm</quantity>
HL, 254+ mm TL; examined here). The occurrence of 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFEDF871BDD43C44CFB3A7B48" baseAuthorityName="Gilbert" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[1110,1245,1635,1661]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="265" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="burragei">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEDF871BDD43C44CFB3A7B48" box="[1110,1245,1635,1661]" italics="true" pageId="265" pageNumber="266">N. burragei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="47AF43B9FEDF871BDC1FC44CFAAE7B4B" box="[1290,1353,1636,1662]" name="Japan" pageId="265" pageNumber="266">Japan</collectingCountry>
is quite dubious, considering that no additional specimens have been obtained despite the relatively shallow occurrence of the species and extensive trawl surveys in southern 
<collectingCountry id="47AF43B9FEDF871BDA3FC4C4FC8E7A33" box="[810,873,1772,1798]" name="Japan" pageId="265" pageNumber="266">Japan</collectingCountry>
over the past several decades. Citing 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEDF871BDC30C4C3FC937A1D" author="Kamohara, T." pageId="265" pageNumber="266" pagination="186 - 190" refId="ref290602" refString="Kamohara, T. (1937) On some rare and one new species of fishes from Japan. Dobutsugaku Zasshi [Zoological Magazine, Japan], 49, 186 - 190. [In Japanese with English abstract.]" type="journal article" year="1937">Kamohara’s (1937)</bibRefCitation>
record, all subsequent authors have believed 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFEDF871BDC87C526FC6B7A7F" baseAuthorityName="Gilbert" baseAuthorityYear="1905" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="265" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="burragei">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEDF871BDC87C526FC6B7A7F" italics="true" pageId="265" pageNumber="266">N. burragei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to occur in Japanese waters (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEDF871BDC23C518FC827A59" author="Matsubara, K." pageId="265" pageNumber="266" refId="ref293415" refString="Matsubara, K. (1955) Fish Morphology and Hierarchy. Ishizaki Shoten, Tokyo, xi + v + 1950 + viii pp., 135 pls. [In Japanese.]" type="book" year="1955">Matsubara 1955</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEDF871BDA6EC57AFBDA7A59" author="Okamura, O." box="[891,1085,1874,1900]" pageId="265" pageNumber="266" refId="ref297275" refString="Okamura, O. (1970 a) Fauna Japonica, Macrourina (Pisces). Academic Press of Japan, Tokyo, 216 pp., 64 pls." type="book" year="1970">Okamura 1970a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEDF871BDD46C57AFB7C7A59" author="Okamura, O." box="[1107,1179,1874,1900]" pageId="265" pageNumber="266" pagination="93 - 99" refId="ref297499" refString="Okamura, O. (1984 b) Macrouroidei. In: Masuda, H., Amaoka, K., Araga, C., Uyeno, T. &amp; Yoshino, T. (Eds.), The Fishes of the Japanese Archipelago. 1 st Edition. Tokai University Press, Tokyo, pp. 93 - 99, pls. 79 - 83. [In Japanese.]" type="book chapter" year="1984">1984b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEDF871BDDA7C57AFB0A7A59" author="Okamura, O." box="[1202,1261,1874,1900]" pageId="265" pageNumber="266" pagination="344 - 373" refId="ref297606" refString="Okamura, O. (1988) Macrouroidei. In: Masuda, H., Amaoka, K., Araga, C., Uyeno, T. &amp; Yoshino, T. (Eds.), The Fishes of the Japanese Archipelago. 2 nd Edition. Tokai University Press, Tokyo, pp. 93 - 99, 453, pls. 79 - 83, 344 - 373." type="journal article" year="1988">1988</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEDF871BDC11C57AFA407A59" author="Nakabo, T." box="[1284,1447,1874,1900]" pageId="265" pageNumber="266" pagination="1276 - 1277" refId="ref295357" refString="Nakabo, T. (1993) Macrouridae. In: Nakabo, T. (Ed.), Fishes of Japan with Pictorial Keys to the Species. 1 st Edition. Tokai University Press, Tokyo, pp. 353 - 371, 1276 - 1277. [In Japanese.]" type="journal article" year="1993">Nakabo 1993</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEDF871BDA3FC55CFC827ABB" author="Nakabo, T." box="[810,869,1908,1934]" pageId="265" pageNumber="266" pagination="417 - 435" refId="ref295412" refString="Nakabo, T. (2000) Macrouridae. In: Nakabo, T. (Ed.), Fishes of Japan with Pictorial Keys to the Species. 2 nd Edition. Tokai University Press, Tokyo, pp. 417 - 435, 1494. [In Japanese.]" type="journal article" year="2000">2000</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEDF871BDA65C55CFC4C7ABB" author="Nakabo, T." box="[880,939,1908,1934]" pageId="265" pageNumber="266" pagination="1491 - 1492" refId="ref295465" refString="Nakabo, T. (2002) Macrouridae. In: Nakabo, T. (Ed.), Fishes of Japan with Pictorial Keys to the Species. English Edition. Tokai University Press, Tokyo, pp. 417 - 435, 1491 - 1492. [In Japanese.]" type="journal article" year="2002">2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEDF871BDAA2C55CFB4C7ABB" author="Shinohara, G. &amp; Endo, H. &amp; Matsuura, K. &amp; Machida, Y. &amp; Honda, H." box="[951,1195,1908,1934]" pageId="265" pageNumber="266" pagination="283 - 343" refId="ref299992" refString="Shinohara, G., Endo, H., Matsuura, K., Machida, Y. &amp; Honda, H. (2001) Annotated checklist of the deepwater fishes from Tosa Bay, Japan. National Science Museum Tokyo Monographs, (20), 283 - 343." type="journal article" year="2001">
Shinohara 
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEDF871BDD25C55CFB8E7ABB" box="[1072,1129,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="265" pageNumber="266">et al.</emphasis>
2001
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEDF871BDDA2C55CFA787ABB" author="Nakabo, T. &amp; Kai, Y." box="[1207,1439,1908,1934]" pageId="265" pageNumber="266" pagination="1872 - 1876" refId="ref295555" refString="Nakabo, T. &amp; Kai, Y. (2013) Macrouridae. In: Nakabo, T. (Ed.), Fishes of Japan with Pictorial Keys to the Species. 3 rd Edition. Tokai University Press, Hadano, pp. 493 - 512, 1872 - 1876. [In Japanese.]" type="journal article" year="2013">Nakabo &amp; Kai 2013</bibRefCitation>
). Unfortunately, the voucher specimen of 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEDF871BDDF2C5BEFA4C7A85" author="Kamohara, T." box="[1255,1451,1942,1968]" pageId="265" pageNumber="266" pagination="186 - 190" refId="ref290602" refString="Kamohara, T. (1937) On some rare and one new species of fishes from Japan. Dobutsugaku Zasshi [Zoological Magazine, Japan], 49, 186 - 190. [In Japanese with English abstract.]" type="journal article" year="1937">Kamohara (1937)</bibRefCitation>
was apparently lost during the WWII, which makes it difficult to reconfirm the Japanese record of this species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3F070329FEDF8718DA3FC5D4FD4D7523" blockId="265.[810,1452,1431,2070]" lastBlockId="266.[136,778,1499,2070]" lastPageId="266" lastPageNumber="267" pageId="265" pageNumber="266">
However, 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEDF871BDAB1C5D4FB647523" author="Kamohara, T." box="[932,1155,2044,2070]" pageId="265" pageNumber="266" pagination="186 - 190" refId="ref290602" refString="Kamohara, T. (1937) On some rare and one new species of fishes from Japan. Dobutsugaku Zasshi [Zoological Magazine, Japan], 49, 186 - 190. [In Japanese with English abstract.]" type="journal article" year="1937">Kamohara’s (1937)</bibRefCitation>
specimen appears to be attributable to a different species of 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFEDC8718DB53C7F4FD4F78C0" authorityName="Jordan in Jordan &amp; Starks" authorityYear="1904" box="[582,680,1500,1525]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEDC8718DB53C7F4FD4F78C0" box="[582,680,1500,1525]" italics="true" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">Nezumia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, due to notable differences between his figure (
<figureCitation id="A7831FACFEDC8718DB70C7D5FD2C7B2D" box="[613,715,1533,1560]" captionStart="FIGURE 180" captionStartId="266.[136,235,1331,1355]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,159,1299]" captionTargetId="figure-314@266.[151,1436,159,1299]" captionTargetPageId="266" captionText="FIGURE 180. Drawing of a species of Nezumia illustrated by Toshiji Kamohara (deposited at BSKU). The illustrated specimen, which was destroyed during WWII, was the basis for the first Japanese record of N. burragei by Kamohara (1937). [Photo: BSKU]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6423172" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6423172/files/figure.png" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">Fig. 180</figureCitation>
) and the 
<typeStatus id="E003BD8BFEDC8718D9A6C437FEF27B0C" box="[179,277,1567,1593]" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFEDC8718D82BC408FE257B0C" baseAuthorityName="Gilbert" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[318,450,1567,1593]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="burragei">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEDC8718D82BC408FE257B0C" box="[318,450,1567,1593]" italics="true" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">N. burragei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEDC8718DB15C437FD737B0F" author="Gilbert, C. H." box="[512,660,1567,1594]" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" pagination="573 - 713" refId="ref285669" refString="Gilbert, C. H. (1905) The deep-sea fishes of the Hawaiian Islands. In: Jordan, D. S. &amp; Evermann, B. W. (Eds.), The Aquatic Resources of the Hawaiian Islands. Bulletin of the U. S. Fish Commission, 23. Government Printing Office, Washington DC, pp. 573 - 713, figs. 230 - 276, pls. 66 - 101. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 12624" type="book chapter" year="1905">Gilbert 1905</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 260). 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEDC8718D99DC469FEB77B69" author="Kamohara, T." box="[136,336,1601,1628]" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" pagination="186 - 190" refId="ref290602" refString="Kamohara, T. (1937) On some rare and one new species of fishes from Japan. Dobutsugaku Zasshi [Zoological Magazine, Japan], 49, 186 - 190. [In Japanese with English abstract.]" type="journal article" year="1937">Kamohara (1937)</bibRefCitation>
illustrated his specimen as having the ventral surface of the snout only narrowly naked above the upper lip, and the posterior margin of the naked area not extending beyond a vertical through the anterior rim of the orbit. In contrast, the ventral surface of the snout and the lower half of the suborbital area are completely naked in the 
<typeStatus id="E003BD8BFEDC8718D9D9C525FEC97A12" box="[204,302,1805,1831]" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFEDC8718D844C526FE357A12" baseAuthorityName="Gilbert" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[337,466,1805,1831]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="burragei">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEDC8718D844C526FE357A12" box="[337,466,1805,1831]" italics="true" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">N. burragei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with the hind margin of the naked area extending to above the posterior margin of the upper jaw. The difference between the two specimens is also evident in the dorsal contour of the head. 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEDC8718DB96C55CFF357A85" author="Kamohara, T." pageId="266" pageNumber="267" pagination="186 - 190" refId="ref290602" refString="Kamohara, T. (1937) On some rare and one new species of fishes from Japan. Dobutsugaku Zasshi [Zoological Magazine, Japan], 49, 186 - 190. [In Japanese with English abstract.]" type="journal article" year="1937">Kamohara’s (1937)</bibRefCitation>
figure shows that the predorsal contour of his specimen was prominently humped over the nape, whereas in the 
<typeStatus id="E003BD8BFEDC8718D9C5C5F2FED37AC1" box="[208,308,2010,2036]" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">holotype</typeStatus>
, the dorsal contour of the head is straight from above the orbit to the first dorsal-fin origin.
</paragraph>
<caption id="6BC753A1FEDC8718D99DC71BFF3378BA" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6423172" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6423172" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6423172/files/figure.png" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" startId="266.[136,235,1331,1355]" targetBox="[151,1436,159,1299]" targetPageId="266">
<paragraph id="3F070329FEDC8718D99DC71BFF3378BA" blockId="266.[136,1452,1331,1423]" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEDC8718D99DC71BFEF9787E" bold="true" box="[136,286,1331,1355]" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">FIGURE 180.</emphasis>
Drawing of a species of 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFEDC8718DB0AC71CFD9F787E" authorityName="Jordan in Jordan &amp; Starks" authorityYear="1904" box="[543,632,1332,1355]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEDC8718DB0AC71CFD9F787E" box="[543,632,1332,1355]" italics="true" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">Nezumia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
illustrated by Toshiji Kamohara (deposited at BSKU). The illustrated specimen, which was destroyed during WWII, was the basis for the first Japanese record of 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFEDC8718DAE7C77EFB8B7858" baseAuthorityName="Gilbert" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[1010,1132,1365,1389]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="burragei">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEDC8718DAE7C77EFB8B7858" box="[1010,1132,1365,1389]" italics="true" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">N. burragei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEDC8718DD8CC77DFAB37858" author="Kamohara, T." box="[1177,1364,1365,1389]" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" pagination="186 - 190" refId="ref290602" refString="Kamohara, T. (1937) On some rare and one new species of fishes from Japan. Dobutsugaku Zasshi [Zoological Magazine, Japan], 49, 186 - 190. [In Japanese with English abstract.]" type="journal article" year="1937">Kamohara (1937)</bibRefCitation>
. [Photo: BSKU]
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="3F070329FEDC8718DA4AC7F4FAE87AE7" blockId="266.[810,1452,1499,2002]" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">
It is most likely that the record of 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEDC8718DDF1C7F3FA4C78C3" author="Kamohara, T." box="[1252,1451,1499,1526]" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" pagination="186 - 190" refId="ref290602" refString="Kamohara, T. (1937) On some rare and one new species of fishes from Japan. Dobutsugaku Zasshi [Zoological Magazine, Japan], 49, 186 - 190. [In Japanese with English abstract.]" type="journal article" year="1937">Kamohara (1937)</bibRefCitation>
represents a misidentification of 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFEDC8718DD9AC7D6FB077B22" box="[1167,1248,1534,1559]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rara" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEDC8718DD9AC7D6FB077B22" box="[1167,1248,1534,1559]" italics="true" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">N. rara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEDC8718DDF1C7D6FADC7B2D" bold="true" box="[1252,1339,1534,1560]" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="16FF6240FEDC8718DDF1C7D6FADC7B2D" box="[1252,1339,1534,1560]" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
described here. Many features of his specimen, including fin-ray counts, head squamation, and the general appearance, agree well with those of the new species. Another possibility is that his specimen was a representative of 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFEDC8718DA3FC480FC4B7BF4" authorityName=": Okamura" authorityYear="1970" box="[810,940,1704,1729]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="proxima">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEDC8718DA3FC480FC4B7BF4" box="[810,940,1704,1729]" italics="true" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">N. proxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Smith &amp; Radcliffe 
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEDC8718DDBEC480FB267BF4" box="[1195,1217,1704,1729]" italics="true" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">in</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEDC8718DDDBC48FFA627BF7" author="Radcliffe, L." box="[1230,1413,1703,1730]" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" pagination="105 - 140" refId="ref298180" refString="Radcliffe, L. (1912) Description of a new family, two new genera, and twenty-nine new species of anacanthine fishes from the Philippine Islands and contiguous waters. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 43, 105 - 140, pls. 22 - 31. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.43 - 1924.105" type="journal article" year="1912">Radcliffe, 1912</bibRefCitation>
), a moderately common species at upper and mid-slope depths in the Pacific off southern 
<collectingCountry id="47AF43B9FEDC8718DD7AC4C4FB557A33" box="[1135,1202,1772,1798]" name="Japan" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">Japan</collectingCountry>
. Although Kamohara extensively surveyed the deep demersal fishes of Tosa Bay and adjacent waters, he did not record 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFEDC8718DDC8C518FABD7A7C" authorityName=": Okamura" authorityYear="1970" box="[1245,1370,1840,1865]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="proxima">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEDC8718DDC8C518FABD7A7C" box="[1245,1370,1840,1865]" italics="true" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">N. proxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
during his career. 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFEDC8718DABFC57AFB9F7A59" baseAuthorityName="Gilbert" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[938,1144,1874,1900]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="burragei">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEDC8718DABFC57AFB9F7A59" box="[938,1144,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">Nezumia burragei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be confined to the Hawaiian Archipelago, and is unlikely to occur in Japanese waters. Therefore, this species is excluded from the list of Japanese grenadiers in this study.
</paragraph>
